This paper deals with the application of transfer learning in Reinforcement Learning, which is a subfield of Machine Learning. The paper proposes a deep architecture for adaptive policy transfer, which involves the use of neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves simulations and evaluations, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-categories.
